# ENDOS Dynamic Knowledge Graph – Sprint 5.1

## Purpose

Sprint 5.1 introduces the first interactive ENDOS object graph. The goal is to move beyond static documentation and represent ENDOS as a connected system of engines, methods, patents, publications, validation cases, pilot domains and architecture objects.

## Included capabilities

- Clickable graph nodes
- Dragging of individual nodes
- Canvas panning
- Mouse-wheel zoom
- Search across node names, IDs, types, status and descriptions
- Filter chips by object type
- Detail panel with metadata
- Relationship buttons for navigation between connected objects
- JSON-based graph data model in `data/endos-graph.json`

## Main files

- `pages/knowledge-graph.html`
- `assets/js/graph.js`
- `data/endos-graph.json`
- `assets/css/style.css`

## Object types

- Platform
- Engine
- Knowledge Object
- Method
- Patent
- Publication
- Validation Case
- Pilot
- Repository

## Next development step

Sprint 5.2 should connect the graph to a larger object register and introduce object IDs, evidence strength, source references, maturity scoring and patent-family mapping.
